import datetime,time
TW2330_df_with_time = TW2330_df.reset_index()
TW2330_df_with_time["Date"] = TW2330_df_with_time["Date"].map(lambda xx:time.mktime(xx.timetuple()))


fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2)
TW2330_df[["Open","High","Low","Close"]].tail(100).plot(ax=axes[0])

from matplotlib.finance import candlestick,candlestick2
candlestick(axes[1],TW2330_df_with_time[["Date","Open","High","Low","Close"]].tail(100).values,
            width=2,colorup="g",colordown="r")

Which Models is the best ?

How to get the Best Model?

Solving of Optimization Problems:

Linear Programming:

\[ \begin{eqnarray} \min_{x_1,x_2} x_1 & + & x_2 \\ 2x_1 & + & x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 & + & 3x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 &&& \geq 0 \\ x_2 &&& \geq 0 \\ \end{eqnarray}\]

Min-Max Problem:

\[ \begin{eqnarray} \min_{x_1,x_2} \max( x_1 & , & x_2 ) \\ 2x_1 & + & x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 & + & 3x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 &&& \geq 0 \\ x_2 &&& \geq 0 \\ \end{eqnarray}\]

Quadratic Programming:

\[ \begin{eqnarray} \min_{x_1,x_2} x_1^2 & + & 9x_2^2 \\ 2x_1 & + & x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 & + & 3x_2 & \geq 1 \\ x_1 &&& \geq 0 \\ x_2 &&& \geq 0 \\ \end{eqnarray}\]
